Hardwork vs Connection

Some people think that individual hard work and abilities are the most important factors for success. Others believe that connections and having a wide network of contacts are more important. Discuss both views and state your opinion.


With increasing technological advancement, particularly the looming possibility of artificial intelligence replacing human labor, people are inclined to work harder and hone their skills to avoid losing their jobs. Many people believe that personal effort is key to success. Others, 	however, argue that building valuable connections play a far more essential role. This essay will examine both perspectives before exlaining why I believe a balanced combination of the two is essential in today's world.




This phenomenon is especially pronounced in China, where the labor force is abundant but the number of available jobs is not fully guaranteed, leading to a social climate where working overtime has become the norm.








